  "body": "### Problem\r\nIn our workflow, when making changes related to `status-go`, it's customary to modify the `status-go-version.json` file, pointing it to a branch rather than a release tag. However, it is easy to overlook this step, leading to the unintentional merging of PRs without pushing a new tag and updating the `status-go` version to point to that tag, causing inconsistencies and issues in our codebase.\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\nWe can implement a new safeguard in our workflow. When a PR modifies the `status-go-version.json` file and points to a branch, it will be automatically blocked from merging. This safeguard will remind contributors to create a release tag and update the status-go version to the new tag before proceeding with the merge.",
